The paper discusses the Lottery Ticket Hypothesis, which is a recent development in the field of deep learning. The paper focuses on the three critical components of the Lottery Ticket algorithm and provides new insights into why LT networks perform as well as they do. The paper also introduces the concept of Supermasks, which can be applied to an untrained, randomly initialized network to produce a model with performance far better than chance. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
